Name: Apple iPad 1st Generation 16GB, Wi-Fi, 9.7in - Black (MB292LL/A) A1219
Product Information: The portable computing revolution started with this 16 GB Apple 1st Generation iPad (Model MB292LL/a). This powerful and reliable touchscreen computer tablet provides users with features such as a 9.7-inch LED display. This device runs iOS 5.1.1, operates over Wi-Fi, and is Bluetooth compatible.Apple products are known for style, and this sleek black tablet is no exception. The device incorporates an Apple A4 processor and multi-touch screen technology. The 1st Generation Apple iPad can help you interface and communicate with family, friends, and co-workers. The Apple iPad connects easily to a Wi-Fi internet connection. The Apple tablet can sync to your computer via a Micro-USB cord or connect over a wireless network.This Apple model is ideal for playing games, using apps, viewing movies, or watching streaming videos on the 1024 x 768 pixel screen. You'll have 16GB of included storage for downloaded books, movies, music, and more. The high-resolution display will allow you to view all your favorites in crisp color.The easy-to-use touch screen makes the reading of eBooks or documents stress-free. Whether you are reading for work or pleasure, you'll have the opportunity to resize your font and change other options that take full advantage of the power of digital text. With just a touch, you'll be holding a large-print book, listening to text-to-speech audio, or adjusting the light levels. You can surf the internet with ease via Wi-Fi or create documents using just the touch of your finger.This 16GB Apple iPad has built-in speakers and an audio jack for headphones. This device can store a large collection of your favorite music and play it back on demand. Whether you are a fan of classic rock or classic Bach, you'll be able to organize playlists and broadcast your music for your own enjoyment or the enjoyment of a crowd.Apple iPads are also tremendous productivity tools for business at home or on the road. The rechargeable battery can keep you working for up to 10 hours. With a built-in keyboard on the screen, you don't need to carry any other accessories to create documents, make notes, or utilize the wide variety of apps available for the iPad via the legacy app download option in the iTunes store. With over two million apps to choose from, you are bound to find many to enhance your work and personal life.The 1st Generation iPad is known for its sturdiness, making it an attractive device for people on the go or families with children. iPads are also fantastic educational tools for students of all ages. The interactivity and tactile learning modes work well for reluctant learners and exceptional students alike. For young learners, iPad games can make education fun for children. Product Information: The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch is an e-reader for people who love reading but don’t want to lug around heavy books. With the Nook, you’ll never have to worry about running out of great beach books while on vacation. If you’re a student, you can say goodbye to backaches caused by carting around heavy textbooks in your backpack. The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch weighs in at just 7.5 ounces, which is less than a paperback book.  At 5 inches by 5 inches by 7 inches, this Nook Simple Touch device is extremely thin. It slips easily into a purse, a backpack, or a jacket pocket, and you can upload up to 1,000 books, magazines, and newspapers into it. Its long-lasting battery allows you to read for weeks at a time on a single charge. If you want to increase the size of your portable library, simply add more memory. This Nook model comes with a 2GB hard drive, but you can add up to 32GB. Simply use the microSD slot on the right side of the unit to install your extra memory. Barnes & Noble is the world’s largest bookstore, so you’ll have access to more than two million titles. Most of these titles are available for less than physical copies, and thousands are actually free. Your Nook also enables you to borrow eBooks from your local public library. This e-reader relies on e-ink Pearl technology, which provides a contrast range that’s 50% greater than its Nook predecessors. The contrast ratio is very close to what you’ll find in a paperback book. This results in sharper, more legible text on the screen so that you’ll be able to read more quickly with greater ease. You’ll even be able to read books comfortably if you’re sitting in bright sunlight. The Nook Simple Touch has a 6-inch display screen you can customize to match your reading preferences. With a touch of your finger, you can choose the font style that’s easiest on your eyes and can use the touchscreen to make the text bigger or smaller. You can bookmark pages, highlight passages you may want to remember, and look up unfamiliar words as well. The Nook Touch reader uses an Android operating system and has built-in support for Wi-Fi. Some Nook owners use this Wi-Fi capability to customize their devices with apps and games. If you want to connect to an external Wi-Fi network, a browser page will pop up, allowing you to sign on. The Nook Simple Touch reader is an attractive matte black, and it’s ergonomically designed to balance easily in one hand. Turn it on and off using the power button, which is located on the top of the back of the unit. Toward the bottom of the back is the USB port that’s used to charge the unit. The USB port can also be used to transfer content from your computer. The buttons on either side of the “N” insignia at the bottom of the Nook’s front are for turning pages. The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch is a wonderful device for anyone who loves tablets but also loves reading books.

Product Information: The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch is an e-reader for people who love reading but don’t want to lug around heavy books. With the Nook, you’ll never have to worry about running out of great beach books while on vacation. If you’re a student, you can say goodbye to backaches caused by carting around heavy textbooks in your backpack. The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch weighs in at just 7.5 ounces, which is less than a paperback book.  At 5 inches by 5 inches by 7 inches, this Nook Simple Touch device is extremely thin. It slips easily into a purse, a backpack, or a jacket pocket, and you can upload up to 1,000 books, magazines, and newspapers into it. Its long-lasting battery allows you to read for weeks at a time on a single charge. If you want to increase the size of your portable library, simply add more memory. This Nook model comes with a 2GB hard drive, but you can add up to 32GB. Simply use the microSD slot on the right side of the unit to install your extra memory. Barnes & Noble is the world’s largest bookstore, so you’ll have access to more than two million titles. Most of these titles are available for less than physical copies, and thousands are actually free. Your Nook also enables you to borrow eBooks from your local public library. This e-reader relies on e-ink Pearl technology, which provides a contrast range that’s 50% greater than its Nook predecessors. The contrast ratio is very close to what you’ll find in a paperback book. This results in sharper, more legible text on the screen so that you’ll be able to read more quickly with greater ease. You’ll even be able to read books comfortably if you’re sitting in bright sunlight. The Nook Simple Touch has a 6-inch display screen you can customize to match your reading preferences. With a touch of your finger, you can choose the font style that’s easiest on your eyes and can use the touchscreen to make the text bigger or smaller. You can bookmark pages, highlight passages you may want to remember, and look up unfamiliar words as well. The Nook Touch reader uses an Android operating system and has built-in support for Wi-Fi. Some Nook owners use this Wi-Fi capability to customize their devices with apps and games. If you want to connect to an external Wi-Fi network, a browser page will pop up, allowing you to sign on. The Nook Simple Touch reader is an attractive matte black, and it’s ergonomically designed to balance easily in one hand. Turn it on and off using the power button, which is located on the top of the back of the unit. Toward the bottom of the back is the USB port that’s used to charge the unit. The USB port can also be used to transfer content from your computer. The buttons on either side of the “N” insignia at the bottom of the Nook’s front are for turning pages. The Barnes & Noble Nook Simple Touch is a wonderful device for anyone who loves tablets but also loves reading books.

Product Information: The Samsung Galaxy Tab S 8.4 takes its name from its 8.4-inch screen, which is a comfortable size for holding in the hand. This device features an Android operating system that allows for maximum compatibility, ease of use, and a wide range of available apps. It is a portable yet powerful option for those who require flexibility but don't want to compromise on capability. This product is also an excellent choice for those who want a tablet suitable for mobile gaming or serving as a mobile workstation. You'll be impressed by the brilliant colors and intuitive design of this model SM-T700.The Galaxy Tab S 8.4 is built around the Exynos 5 Octa Processor, which is consists of four 1.9 GHz Cortex-A15 and four 1.3 GHz Cortex-A7 cores. These cores work in concert with an Exynos 5420 Octa chipset motherboard. This octa-core system is used in these Samsung tablets to provide superior multitasking capability that allows users to run multiple programs simultaneously. Capable of running up to eight processes simultaneously without any slowdown, the device is ideal for juggling multiple messaging systems and viewing streams simultaneously. The SM-T700 uses a Mali-T628 MP6 GPU for graphical processing and has 3 GB of RAM. The Internal memory is 16 GB and can be expanded up to 256 GB via the MicroSD card slot. Additional cloud storage can be obtained using Google Drive or DropBox. Bluetooth, Wi-Fi, and infrared connectivity is also available. A GPS antenna is included as well for location services. The system is powered by a 4900 mAh lithium polymer battery, which lasts for up to 11 hours of continuous usage before needing a recharge.The 8.4-inch Super AMOLED screen can display up to 1600 by 2560 pixels at a 359 PPI density. This allows users to enjoy full HD video on the Galaxy Tab, which can display up to 16 million colors. The Galaxy screen has MultiTouch capability via the Samsung TouchWiz UI. The rear-facing 8 MP camera has autofocus, LED flash, and automatic geo-tagging capabilities. The front-facing 2.1 MP camera is optimized for video conferencing and a great choice for selfies. In addition, this tablet is optimized for media streaming from YouTube, Google TV, and other services. The tablet has a built-in microphone for live conferencing or for use with phone software to make VOIP calls.Originally released in 2014, this Samsung Galaxy runs Android OS KitKat version 4.4.2. The operating system can be upgraded up to Android Marshmallow version 6.0. The manufacturer has included some exclusive apps, and you can connect easily to the Google Play store to download your favorites. The Google productivity suite, which includes Gmail, Gchat, Google Drive and Google Office, is pre-installed. The Chrome browser is built in, although Samsung has provided a default browser if preferred. Users can type in information or check their messages using either the Samsung or Google built-in keyboard programs. The tablet is compatible with third party virtual and physical keyboards. This enables the Samsung Galaxy Tab to function as a desktop replacement device if needed.
